YouTube Channel Create and Setup
YouTube Channels are 2 types
- User Channel
- Brand Channel
 
-	By using one Google (Gmail) account, you can create 1 User Channel and 99 Brand Channel
To create a YouTube account, you actually need a Google (Gmail) account (because YouTube is owned by Google). Here’s how you can do it step by step:

Step-1
-------------------
1. Create a Google (Gmail) Account
- Go to: https://accounts.google.com/signup 
2.	Enter your details: 
- Name 
- Username (this will be your Gmail address) 
- Password 
- Click Next 
- Add your phone number (for verification) 
- Enter the verification code sent to your phone 
- Fill in other details (birthday, gender) 
- Agree to Google’s terms 

✅ Now your Google account is ready.
________________________________________
2. Sign in to YouTube
-	Go to https://www.youtube.com 
-	Click Sign In (top right corner) 
-	Enter your Google email and password 
________________________________________
3. Create a YouTube Channel (Optional but important)
If you want to upload videos:
-	Click your profile icon (top right) 
-	Click “Create a Channel” 
-	Name: All Web Developer (Choose your channel name)
-	Picture: select logo of All Web Developer
-	Click on “Create Channel” button
________________________________________
Now setup your channel
-	Upload Banner Image 
a.	Go to canva.com
b.	In dashboard, click on “Custom Size”  select “Social Media” YouTube  YouTube Banner
c.	Select a design 
d.	Edit design according to your needed
e.	Download image
 
-	Description: write a proper description about your channel
-	Contact Info: your email
-	Video Watermark: 
a.	Go to canva.com
b.	Custom size: 150x150px
c.	Upload: your channel logo
d.	Select logo and set in Canva page
e.	Download it (with transparent background)
f.	In Video Watermark of your YouTube channel, upload the logo (150x150)      https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vieFLDSsXco
g.	Display Time: Enter Video

-	After all done, check all the things
-	If ok, click on “Publish” button to save the settings

Done!

